the offence for which the heaviest penalty is imposed. Where the same disposal is imposed for two or more offences, the offence selected is the offence for which the statutory maximum penalty is the most severe. (4) Every effort is made to ensure that the figures presented are accurate and complete. However, it is important to note that these data have been extracted from large administrative data systems generated by the courts and police forces. As a consequence, care should be taken to ensure data collection processes and their inevitable limitations are taken into account when those data are used. (5) Excludes data for Cardiff magistrates' court for April, July and August 2008.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Justice Statistics Analytical Services - Ministry of Justice Ref: PQC16879</p><p>.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429125/answer",,,,,"16790","2015-11-24T10:58:54.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429125/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429125/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-11-18","Dangerous Dogs Act 1991: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many people in Wales have been prosecuted under sections (a) 1(3), (b) 3(1) and (c) 3(3) of the Dangerous Dogs Act 1991 in each year since 1991; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Angela Smith","Penistone and Stocksbridge","Angela Smith","16879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429126","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-23","<p>Prisoners serving indeterminate sentences have a minimum term, or tariff, imposed by the court for the purposes of punishment and deterrence. Once this has been served release is determined by the Parole Board on the basis of risk.</p><p>The latest figures for the indeterminate sentence prison population by tariff length and tariff expiry date can be found in table 1.9 of the Offender Management Statistics Quarterly Bulletin published on 29 0ctober 2015: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/offender-management-statistics-quarterly-april-to-june-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/offender-management-statistics-quarterly-april-to-june-2015</a></p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429126/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T13:01:02.13Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429126/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429126/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-18","Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisoners are serving sentences beyond the limit of the tariff for the crimes for which they were sentenced.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","16922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429127","Department of Health","false","2015-11-23","<p>Whilst healthcare wings within some prisons provide 24 hour health care, beds within these units are not specifically designated for mental health and may be used by prisoners with a range of physical or mental health problems.</p><br />","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429127/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T16:45:27.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429127/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429127/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-18","Prisons: Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many mental health in-patient units and beds there have been in English prisons in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","16929"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429128","Home Office","false","2015-11-23","<p>The previous Government ring-fenced nearly Â£40 million â Â£10 million per year â of stable funding up until 2015 for specialist local domestic and sexual violence support services, rape crisis centres, the national domestic violence helplines and stalking helpline. This funding has been extended until April 2016 and includes part-funding for 144 Independent Domestic Violence Advisers (IDVAs) and 87 Independent Sexual Violence Advisers (ISVAs).</p><p>The Home Office supports these roles through training and awareness-raising, including for the majority of IDVAs and ISVAs who are employed by local authorities and third sector organisations.</p><p>We recognise the importance of specialist support services and are working with voluntary sector partners and local commissioners to assess coverage and need for these specialist advisers.</p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429128/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T16:55:32.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429128/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429128/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-11-18","Domestic Abuse and Sexual Offences: Victim Support Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate she has made of the number of (a) independent domestic violence advisers and (b) independent sexual violence advisers operating in the criminal justice system in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Catherine McKinnell","Newcastle upon Tyne North","Catherine McKinnell","16840"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429129","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-11-23","<p>Officials in my Department have worked with colleagues at the Department for Work and Pensions to support the application of the Family Test in policy development. All policy teams within the Ministry of Justice have been made aware of the processes to be followed when applying the Test. In line with DWP guidance, potential impacts of policy on family functioning and relationships should be identified and brought to the attention of Ministers where appropriate. The guidance can be located at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/368894/family-test-guidance.pdf</a></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429129/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T17:34:30.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429129/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429129/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-11-18","Ministry of Justice: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps his Department has taken to embed the family test into its policy making.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","16838"
