"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429208","Department of Health","false","2015-12-01","<p>As at 16 November 2015, the job titles of the officials and other individuals in the Department of Healthâs Voluntary Sector Grants Hub are:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Civil Service Grade / Job Title</p></td><td><p>FTEs</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Grade 7</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Senior Executive Officer (SEO) â Team Leader</p></td><td><p>1.75</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Higher Executive Officer (HEO)</p></td><td><p>1</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Higher Executive Officer (HEO) - Senior Account Manager</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Executive Officer (EO) - Account Manager</p></td><td><p>7</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Job titles provided along with grades in instances where staff share the same job title.</p><br />",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429208/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-01T12:31:57.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429208/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429208/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-18","Department of Health: Grants","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government what are the job titles of the officials and other individuals on the Department of Healthâs Voluntary Sector Grants Hub.","true","Biography information for Lord Blencathra",,"Lord Blencathra","HL3692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429209","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-02","<p>The Government has an ambitious strategy for tackling congestion in our cities and towns and improving performance on our roads. This strategy includes providing significant investment in both our strategic and localroad network, as well as working with highway authorities and Local Enterprise Partnerships to encourage more sustainable transport including buses, light rail and walking and cycling.</p><br /><p>In addition, Part 2 of the Traffic Management Act 2004 (&quot;the Act&quot;) specifically places a Network Management Duty (NMD) on each local traffic authority in England to manage its road network to secure the expeditious movement of traffic on its own network and to facilitate the same on the network of other authorities. Coordination of activities and actions between authorities is an especially important element of network management.</p><br /><p>The Act is intended to provide better conditions for all road users through coordination and proactive management of the road network. It provides a key tool in the Government's strategy to tackle congestion through a range of initiatives including for example, better management of street works in order to minimise disruption and delivering fairer systems for civil parking and traffic enforcement.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429209/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-02T14:57:42.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429209/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429209/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-18","Road Traffic: Urban Areas","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government what action they are taking to deal with traffic congestion in towns and cities.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL3693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429210","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-02","<p>Not by Her Majestyâs Government. This is a devolved matter and so would be for the Welsh Government or the relevant traffic authority in Cardiff.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429210/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-02T15:01:34.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429210/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429210/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-18","Road Traffic: Cardiff","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government whether there has been any research into the effect of the introduction of the Traffic Management Act 2004 on congestion in Cardiff, as opposed to other cities.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL3694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429211","Department for Transport","false","2015-12-02","<p>The Department for Transport has not conducted a specific assessment of the effect that congestion in urban areas is having on the cost and attractiveness of bus travel to travellers.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429211/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-02T15:05:12.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429211/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429211/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-18","Bus Services: Urban Areas","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government what assessment they have made of the effect that congestion in urban areas is having on the cost and attractiveness of bus travel to travellers.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL3695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429212","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-30","<p>The bus market outside London is deregulated, with the vast majority of services provided on a commercial basis by private sector bus operators. The impact of congestion in urban areas on the number of buses that have to remain in service is one for bus operators and local transport authorities to consider.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429212/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-30T12:23:03.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429212/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429212/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-18","Bus Services: Greater Manchester","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government what assessment they have made of the effect of congestion in urban areas on the number of buses that have to remain in service, in particular in Manchester.","false","Biography information for Lord Bradshaw",,"Lord Bradshaw","HL3696"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429213","Department for Education","false","2015-12-02","<p>The Department for Education purchased the Commercial Road site in the name of the Department for Communities and Local Government in June 2015. The site has been leased back to London Metropolitan University until August 2016, after which the site will be developed into a school building. The price paid for the site can be obtained from the land registry.</p>",,"Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429213/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-02T16:44:09.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429213/answer","Biography information for Lord Nash","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429213/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-18","London Metropolitan University","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government whether they have purchased 41â71 Commercial Road, Aldgate, which is currently part of the Sir John Cass Faculty of Art, Architecture and Design, from London Metropolitan University; and if so, (1) when; (2) which department purchased that building; (3) what was the asking price; (4) how much they paid; (5) whether the Sir John Cass Faculty of Art, Architecture and Design is being instructed to vacate the premises, and if so, when; and (6) how they intend to use the building in future.","false","Biography information for The Earl of Clancarty",,"The Earl of Clancarty","HL3697"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429214","The Lord Chairman of Committees","false","2015-11-24","<p>The House of Lords Administration was accredited as a London Living Wage employer in November 2013. We have kept in line with changes to the Living Wage since. No staff employed by the House Administration are paid below the London Living Wage.</p>",,"Lord Laming","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429214/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T11:54:03.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429214/answer","Biography information for Lord Laming","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429214/answer",,,,,"200",,"Chairman of Committees (HoL)","2015-11-18","House of Lords: Living Wage","2","House of Lords","To ask the Chairman of Committees whether any staff of the House of Lords are paid less than the recommended Living Wage for London, and if so, how many and in which departments they work.","false","Biography information for Lord Foulkes of Cumnock",,"Lord Foulkes of Cumnock","HL3698"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429215","Department of Health","false","2015-12-01","<p>NHS Englandâs recent announcement &quot;A healthy NHS workforce&quot;, aims to raise staff awareness and understanding of mental health issues and ensure staff have access to help, support and treatment when they need it.</p><br /><p>âA healthy NHS workforceâ includes, for example, line manager training and, providing NHS staff rapid access to talking therapies. This is currently being tested as part of the Healthy Workforce programme led by NHS England.</p><br /><p>NHS Employers is working with NHS England and Public Health England on improving NHS staff health and wellbeing. They offer extensive information and tools for managers to support their employees who are demonstrating signs of mental health problems, or returning to work following periods of sickness absence.</p><br /><p>These resources, which are only available online, can be found at the following link:</p><br /><p>www.nhsemployers.org/your-workforce/retain-and-improve/staff-experience/health-work-and-wellbeing/protecting-staff-and-preventing-ill-health/supporting-line-managers/managers-guide-on-supporting-workplace-mental-health/supporting-staff-who-are-experiencing-mental-health-problems</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429215/answer",,,,,,"2015-12-01T12:29:17.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429215/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429215/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-18","NHS: Mental Health","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government what policy the NHS has about protecting the mental health of its workforce.","false","Biography information for Baroness Greengross",,"Baroness Greengross","HL3699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429216","Department of Health","false","2015-12-01","<p>The Government has not assessed how many National Health Service employees have attempted, or committed, suicide in each year between 2009 and 2014. The Department does not collect this information centrally.</p><br /><p>However, the Department is not complacent and commissions NHS Employers to support trusts to improve the physical and mental health and wellbeing of their employees, which is the responsibility of employers across the NHS in England.</p><br /><p>NHS Employers is working with NHS England and Public Health England on NHS Englandâs recently announced âA healthy NHS workforce&quot;, a commitment in its Five Year Forward View âwhich includes increasing awareness of and addressing mental health issues affecting NHS staffâ. A copy of the announcement is attached.</p><br />",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429216/answer","Simon Stevens announces major drive to improve health in NHS workplace.docx","Simon Stevens announces major drive to improve health in NHS workplace.docx","A Healthy NHS Workforce announcement","A Healthy NHS Workforce announcement",,"2015-12-01T12:26:03.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429216/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429216/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-18","NHS: Suicide","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government what assessment they have made of how many NHS employees have attempted, or committed, suicide in each year between 2009 and 2014.","false","Biography information for Baroness Greengross",,"Baroness Greengross","HL3700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429217","Department of Health","false","2015-12-01","<p>The Government included in its Mandate to NHS England an objective for them to âmake partnership a successâ. This includes â<em>championing the Time to Change campaign to raise awareness of mental health issues and reduce stigma, including in the NHS workforce</em>â.</p><br /><p>In taking this forward, NHS England recently announced the &quot;A healthy NHS workforce&quot; initiative. This aims to raise staff awareness and understanding of mental health issues, helping to ensure they have access to help, support and treatment when they need it. A copy of the announcement is attached.</p><br /><p>âA healthy NHS workforceâ includes, for example, line manager trainingand, providing NHS staff rapid access to talking therapies. Thisis currently being tested as part of the Healthy Workforce programme led by NHS England.</p><br /><p>In addition, NHS Employers have launched the <em>How are you feeling NHS? </em>toolkit. This has been developed with NHS staff to help bridge a gap in understanding and enable them to: talk openly and regularly about their emotional health; assess the impact emotional wellbeing has on themselves, their colleagues and patients, and help with action planning to enable more good days than bad. The online only resource can be found at:</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.nhsemployers.org/your-workforce/retain-and-improve/staff-experience/health-work-and-wellbeing/protecting-staff-and-preventing-ill-health/how-are-you-feeling-nhs-toolkit" target="_blank">www.nhsemployers.org/your-workforce/retain-and-improve/staff-experience/health-work-and-wellbeing/protecting-staff-and-preventing-ill-health/how-are-you-feeling-nhs-toolkit</a></p><br /> <br />",,"Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429217/answer","Simon Stevens announces major drive to improve health in NHS workplace.docx","Simon Stevens announces major drive to improve health in NHS workplace.docx","A Healthy NHS Workforce announcement","A Healthy NHS Workforce announcement",,"2015-12-01T12:13:47.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429217/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429217/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-18","NHS: Mental Health","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majestyâs Government what action they are taking to address the stigma of mental health problems amongst healthcare workers.","false","Biography information for Baroness Greengross",,"Baroness Greengross","HL3701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/429218","Department of Health","false","2015-12-01","<p>The number of days lost through the sickness of healthcare workers between 2009 and 2014 were:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>England</p></td><td><p>Full Time Equivalent Days Lost to Sickness Absence (includes non-working days)</p></td><td><p>Full Time Equivalent Days Available (includes non-working days)</p></td><td><p>Sickness Absence Rate</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>16,745,315</p></td><td><p>380,199,666</p></td><td><p>4.40%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>15,947,054</p></td><td><p>383,278,845</p></td><td><p>4.16%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>15,555,507</p></td><td><p>377,908,880</p></td><td><p>4.12%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>15,947,518</p></td><td><p>376,187,354</p></td><td><p>4.24%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>15,385,468</p></td><td><p>378,691,376</p></td><td><p>4.06%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>16,423,722</p></td><td><p>386,388,483</p></td><td><p>4.25%</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p><em>Source:</em> Health and Social Care Information Centre</p><br /><p>The Government does not record the cost incurred by the National Health Service due to days lost through the sickness of healthcare workers.</p><br /><p>Employers are responsible for reducing the days lost through sickness of their staff. The Department supports the NHS by commissioning NHS Employers to provide trusts with advice, guidance and good practice on improving NHS staff health and wellbeing which is available on an online only resource at:</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.nhsemployers.org/your-workforce/retain-and-improve/staff-experience/health-work-and-wellbeing/protecting-staff-and-preventing-ill-health/supporting-line-managers/managers-guide-on-supporting-workplace-mental-health/supporting-staff-who-are-experiencing-mental-health-problems" target="_blank">www.nhsemployers.org/your-workforce/