"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428742","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-24","<p>The Department has not made an assessment regarding this issue.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428742/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T15:53:05.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428742/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428742/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-17","Funerals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of introducing statutory regulations of the funeral industry.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","16680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428743","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-25","<p>I have asked my officials to seek an update from Scottish Power on what steps they are taking in this matter.</p>","Bromsgrove","Sajid Javid","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428743/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T17:39:56.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428743/answer","Biography information for Sajid Javid","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428743/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-17","Scottish Power","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what progress has been made towards a resolution of the Scottish Power cashback mis-selling dispute since his meeting in July 2015 with the CEO of the Insolvency Service.","false","Biography information for Richard Arkless","Dumfries and Galloway","Richard  Arkless","16713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428744","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-01-27","<p>The digital sector contributes more than 7 per cent to the UK economy - it is one of our most innovative sectors, and needs a strong skills base to continue to grow and succeed. That is why this Government has implemented the new apprenticeship levy, and is consulting digital and technology employers to have a better understanding of their specific skills needs and assess the likely impacts of the levy on existing professional training programmes and initiatives.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428744/answer",,,,,"16705","2016-01-27T13:58:20.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428744/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428744/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-17","Digital Technology: Skilled Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the current provision of skills required by the digital economy; and what steps he is taking to ensure that training delivered under the apprenticeship levy is geared towards high-value high-skilled jobs.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","16689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428745","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-20","<p>My Rt hon Friend the Chancellor of the Exchequer will announce further details of the apprenticeship levy at the Spending Review, including the scope and rate of the levy.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428745/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T11:09:32.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428745/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428745/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-17","Apprentices: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether businesses will be permitted to allocate their apprenticeship-levied funds to small and medium-sized enterprises and other business in their supply chain; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","16690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428746","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-01-27","<p>The digital sector contributes more than 7 per cent to the UK economy - it is one of our most innovative sectors, and needs a strong skills base to continue to grow and succeed. That is why this Government has implemented the new apprenticeship levy, and is consulting digital and technology employers to have a better understanding of their specific skills needs and assess the likely impacts of the levy on existing professional training programmes and initiatives.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428746/answer",,,,,"16689","2016-01-27T13:58:20.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428746/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428746/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-17","Digital Technology: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of the likely effect of the apprenticeship levy on existing professional training and digital skills initiatives provided by the digital technology industry.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","16705"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428747","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-04-26","<p>Ed Vaizey, Minister for Culture and the Digital Economy, and Anna Soubry, the Small Firms Minister, participated in roundtable discussions on September 10th when the report was launched. We do not propose to formally respond to the FSB report.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428747/answer",,,,,,"2016-04-26T12:54:45.303Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428747/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428747/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-17","Digital Technology: Small Businesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if he will issue a response to the Federation of Small Businesses report, entitled Reassured, optimised, transformed: driving digital small business, published in September 2015.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","16736"
