"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428749","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-20","<p>The Cabinet Office is not forecasting any underspend against departmental expenditure limits in the current fiscal year. There was no underspend forecast at the time of the Summer Budget 2015 or the March Budget 2015 either.</p><p /> <p>The Departmentâs latest forecast of total annually managed expenditure is Â£5 million, in line with the budget for 2015-16.</p><p /> <br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428749/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T13:12:40.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428749/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428749/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-17","Cabinet Office: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what (a) the amount of any underspend expected against departmental expenditure limits in the current fiscal year and (b) his Department's latest forecast of total annually managed expenditure spend for this year is; and what the forecasts were for those sums at the time of the Summer Budget 2015 and March Budget 2015.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","16738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428750","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-20","<p>The Fundraising Preference Service, recommended by the Etherington reviewinto fundraising, will re-balancepower back to individuals and help them to press the 'reset' button on their relationship with fundraisers, giving them control over the fundraisingcommunications they receive from charities. It will stop people being inundated withrequests which they do not wish to receive and it will stop charities wasting resources oncommunicating with people that do not wish to hear from them. It also seeks to underwritepublic trust and confidence in charities which is vital to the sectorâs work.</p><p>A working group involving charities is being established to develop the detailed plans for theimplementation of the service.</p>","Reading East","Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428750/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T11:18:10.493Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428750/answer","Biography information for Mr Rob Wilson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428750/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-17","Charities","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the potential effect of a fundraising preference service on the work of the charity sector.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","16683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428751","Cabinet Office","false","2015-11-20","<p>I refer the Hon. Member to the answer I gave to the Hon. Member for Sheffield, Heeley on 2 November 2015 to UIN: 13799.</p><br />","West Suffolk","Matthew Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428751/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T13:14:24.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428751/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428751/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-11-17","Electronic Government: Data Protection","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what steps he is taking to protect the personal details of those registered with the Government Gateway service from hacking; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","16682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428752","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-20","<p>Since its launch in 2012 the UK Guarantees Scheme has approved Â£3.7bn of guarantees for projects, enabling Â£23bn of projects to commence. In 2015 the UK Guarantees Scheme has, to date, approved Â£2bn of guarantees.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428752/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:03:51.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428752/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428752/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many and what value of projects received guarantees through the UK Guarantees Scheme (a) in 2015 and (b) since that scheme's launch.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","16730"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428753","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-20","<p>Younger workers tend to have less experience than older workers in the labour market, and so there is a risk that too high a wage rate may make them relatively less attractive to employers. So, to minimise any negative impact on employment of younger workers, the National Living Wage is limited to those 25 and over. The Government has not therefore made an estimate of what the fiscal impact of this policy change would be.</p><br /><p>The Office for Budgetary Responsibility estimate that, by 2020-21, the National Living Wage will increase income tax and NICs receipts by around Â£0.1bn, as set out in Table B.3 in of their July 2015 Economic and Fiscal Outlook. They assume that, by 2020-21, the overall impact of the policy on the public finances is to reduce public sector net borrowing by Â£0.2bn.</p><br />","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428753/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:13:09.593Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428753/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428753/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Living Wage: Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will estimate the annual change in tax revenue from extending the national living wage to those aged between 18 and 25.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","16700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428754","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-20","<p>The Paper, âFixing the Foundations: creating a more prosperous economyâ focuses not on the link between welfare reforms and productivity but instead on how âa productive economy must make the most of its labour force and effectively mobilise people into jobsâ.</p><br /><p>This governments tax and welfare policies are supporting this end.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428754/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:16:52.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428754/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428754/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Productivity","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the document, Fixing the Foundations: Creating a more prosperous nation, Cm 9098, published in July 2015, if he will publish his Department's analysis linking changes to tax credits with increased productivity.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","16701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428755","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-20","<p>The 2nd Permanent Secretary to the Treasury explained to the PAC on the 10 December 2014 (see link below) the process for Business Case approvals within Government. The first stage of this process, the Strategic Outline Business Case, was agreed for Universal Credit in September 2014. The next step, the Outline Business Case, is now with Treasury Ministers for approval. The Full Business Case will follow for Ministerial approval by the end of 2017. This is in line with the process within Government and a Programme of the scale and complexity of Universal Credit.</p><p><a href="http://data.parliament.uk/writtenevidence/committeeevidence.svc/evidencedocument/public-accounts-committee/universal-credit-progress-update/oral/16340.html" target="_blank">http://data.parliament.uk/writtenevidence/committeeevidence.svc/evidencedocument/public-accounts-committee/universal-credit-progress-update/oral/16340.html</a></p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428755/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:01:48.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428755/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428755/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, when he expects to sign off in full the business case for universal credit.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","16693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428756","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-20","<p>The Government is introducing a Youth Obligation for 18-21s on Universal Credit, to help them into sustainable employment.</p><br /><p>From day 1 of their claim, young people will participate in an intensive support regime in return for their benefit. After 6 months, we will expect them to apply for an apprenticeship, traineeship, gain work-based skills, or go on a work placement.</p><br /><p>As set out in âFixing the Foundations: Creating a more prosperous nationâ, this is part of the Governmentâs plan for achieving full employment. The Government wants to ensure that young people are given the support, skills and experience to move into work, fulfil their potential and make a contribution to a productive economy.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428756/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:15:24.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428756/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428756/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Productivity","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the document, Fixing the Foundations: Creating a more prosperous nation, Cm 9098, published in July 2015, if he will publish his Department's analysis linking the introduction of a Youth Obligation for 18 to 25 year olds on universal credit with increased productivity.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","16702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428757","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-24","<p>Treasury Ministers have regular discussions with Ministers of the devolved administrations and with politicians of all parties on a range of topics.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428757/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T14:27:21.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428757/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428757/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Welfare Tax Credits: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what discussions he has had with the Northern Ireland Executive on tax credits since 25 October.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","16663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428758","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-20","<p>Officials in my Department have liaised with DWP as the lead Department for the Family Test to embed it into the policy process. This has included training officials on applying the Test, disseminating relevant evidence, learning materials and best practice.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428758/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:20:48.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428758/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428758/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Treasury: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department is taking to embed the family test into its policy making.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","16711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428759","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-24","<p>Estimates of total revenue losses associated with fuel fraud in Northern Ireland are published in chapter 5 of âMeasuring Tax Gaps 2015'. These estimates cannot be disaggregated by type of fraud such as smuggling or laundering.</p><br /><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/measuring-tax-gaps" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/measuring-tax-gaps</a></p><p><br></p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428759/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T14:28:19.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428759/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428759/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Fuels: Tax Evasion","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his estimate is of revenue lost to the Exchequer through fuel laundering in Northern Ireland in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","16637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428760","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-20","<p>The Insurersâ Infrastructure Investment Forum was set up the to give members of the Association of British Insurers (ABI) a direct communication link to Government, exploring ways to maximise opportunities for insurance fund managers to invest in UK infrastructure debt instruments via the capital markets.</p><p>In 2013 a group of 6 insurers agreed to aim to invest Â£25bn in UK infrastructure over the next 5 years. They have already invested over Â£5bn and are on track to meet their target.</p><br /><p>In 2015 InfraRed Capital Partners and Prudential have each taken 45% stakes in the Â£1bn Swansea Bay Tidal Lagoon project.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428760/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:02:55.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428760/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428760/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many and what value of projects received investment through the Infrastructure Investment Forum (a) in 2015 and (b) since the Forum's launch.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Ashworth","Leicester South","Jonathan Ashworth","16739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428761","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-23","<p>The Government currently has no plans to raise the upper trivial commutation limit for pensions above Â£30,000.</p><br /><p>The Government believes this is the appropriate level which balances providing individuals with flexibility without placing a significant administrative burden on pension schemes.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428761/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T16:41:58.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428761/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428761/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Pensions","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what his policy is on raising the upper trivial commutation limit for pensions above Â£30,000.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","16666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428762","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-23","<p>The Department worked with the Local Government Association to provide two guidance documents for local authorities, housing associations and other housing providers on keeping residents safe in the event of a fire and on providing safe means of escape. These publications (<em>Housing â Fire Safety</em> and <em>Fire safety in purpose-built blocks of flats)</em> are both available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/workplace-fire-safety-your-responsibilities/fire-safety-advice-documents" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/workplace-fire-safety-your-responsibilities/fire-safety-advice-documents</a>.</p><p>Government also provides guidance on the requirements under part B of the Building Regulations on design of escape routes in new buildings, available at: <a href="http://www.planningportal.gov.uk/buildingregulations/approveddocuments/partb/bcapproveddocumentsb/bcapproveddocbvol1/" target="_blank">http://www.planningportal.gov.uk/buildingregulations/approveddocuments/partb/bcapproveddocumentsb/bcapproveddocbvol1/</a>.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428762/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T15:41:35.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428762/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428762/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-17","Social Rented Housing: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what guidance his Department publishes to local authorities and housing associations on providing a safe means of exit for disabled residents in the event of an emergency.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","16714"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428763","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-20","<p>To help landlords prepare for introduction of the Smoke and Carbon Monoxide Alarm (England) Regulations 2015, my Department provided Â£3.2 million of non ring-fenced funding to local Fire and Rescue Authorities to purchase and distribute smoke and carbon monoxide alarms to landlords.</p><p>These regulations aim to protect tenants from fire and carbon monoxide poisoning in the home, and to further that aim we would expect Fire and Rescue Authorities to continue distributing any remaining alarms following the introduction of the regulations to help landlords comply, therefore safeguarding more tenants.</p><p>The Chief Fire Officers Association Home Safety Committee are planning to conduct further research and analysis on the distribution of the free alarms in the new year.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428763/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T09:06:38.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428763/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428763/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-17","Private Rented Housing: Safety","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, through what channels his Department plans to disburse the Â£3.2 million payment from the Fire and Rescue Authorities to private landlords for smoke and carbon dioxide alarms after the introduction of the Smoke and Carbon Monoxide Alarm (England) Regulations 2015.","false","Biography information for Mary Creagh","Wakefield","Mary Creagh","16737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428764","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-20","<p>The details of the Chair and terms of reference for the independent review of local council tax support schemes will be published in due course. A Review team comprising four full-time equivalents staff has been set up to provide project and analytical support to the Chair.</p><p>The Review will be completed by the end of March 2016.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428764/answer",,,,,"16642 ; 16643","2015-11-20T11:43:48.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428764/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428764/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-17","Council Tax Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to appoint the Chair of the review of the localisation of council tax benefit; and by what process he plans for that Chair and other people working on that review work to be selected.","false","Biography information for Ms Karen Buck","Westminster North","Ms Karen Buck","16641"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428765","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-20","<p>Forum members agreed to to cancel the June 2015 meeting, as there were no substantive agenda times. Therefore there are no minutes available.</p><br />","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428765/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T11:44:43.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428765/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428765/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-17","Council Tax Reduction Schemes","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will place in the Library the minutes of the meeting of the Council Tax Partnership Forum in June 2015.","false","Biography information for Ms Karen Buck","Westminster North","Ms Karen Buck","16645"
