"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428769","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-11-20","<p>We have made available over Â£500 million to local authorities and the voluntary sector to tackle homelessness. Since 2010, this has helped local authorities to prevent 935,800 households from becoming homeless.</p><p>The attached table (London Borough Homelessness Prevention Grant allocation 2012-13) shows the allocations of Homelessness Prevention Grant in 2012- 13 for London Boroughs.</p><p>From 2013-14 support for preventing homelessness has been included in the annual Local Government Finance Settlement, split between Revenue Support Grant and estimated retained business rates. In the following years London Boroughsâ level of notional grant was as set out in the attached table (London Borough Homelessness Prevention Grant allocation 2013-16).</p><p>Revenue Support Grant and retained business rates are not ring-fenced. It is up to individual authorities to decide how grant funding should be spent in order to deliver local services.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428769/answer","1190070.docx ; 1188773.docx","1190070.docx ; 1188773.docx","London Borough HPG allocation 2012/13 ; London Borough HPG allocation 2013-16","London Borough HPG allocation 2012/13 ; London Borough HPG allocation 2013-16",,"2015-11-20T11:48:48.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428769/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428769/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-11-17","Homelessness: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how much his Department provided in Homelessness Prevention Grant to each local authority in London in (a) 2012-13, (b) 2013-14, (c) 2014-15 and (d) 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Reed","Croydon North","Mr Steve Reed","16726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428770","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-30","<p>Eddisbury is eligible for extra funding sources to increase local superfast broadband coverage, including clawback funding BT are offering in response to the high take-up of superfast broadband in Cheshire. It is for Connecting Cheshire to decide which areas to prioritise funding.</p><p><br>In addition, the Prime Minister recently announced the ambition to give people the legal right to request a connection to broadband with speeds of 10 Mbps, no matter where in the country they live.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428770/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-30T09:56:22.47Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428770/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428770/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-17","Broadband: Cheshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, pursuant to the Answer of 16 November 2015 to Question 15873, on broadband: Cheshire, if he will take steps to  bring the planned coverage of Eddisbury in line with the Cheshire average.","false","Biography information for Antoinette Sandbach","Eddisbury","Antoinette Sandbach","16734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428771","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-23","<p>A public consultation which began on Thursday 16 July and closed on 8 October received in excess of 190,000 responses. We are now in the process of analysing these responses.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428771/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T09:20:18.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428771/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428771/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-17","BBC","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that public opinion is taken into account in its input to the BBC Charter review.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","16633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428772","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-11-25","<p>From 1 November 2010 to 31 October 2015, the Big Lottery Fund in Scotland has allocated monies to over 11,500 projects.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428772/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T15:21:27.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428772/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428772/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-11-17","Big Lottery Fund: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many community projects have benefited from monies allocated by Scotland's Big Lottery Fund in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Owen Thompson","Midlothian","Owen Thompson","16631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428773","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-24","<p>Steel is sourced by our contractors from a range of UK and international suppliers, reflecting the need to ensure competitive cost, time and quality. The Ministry of Defence has not directly made an assessment of the likely effect of redundancies in the UK steel industry but, is represented on the cross-Government steel procurement working group led by the Cabinet Office, and new Government guidelines, which include the need for effective pre-procurement engagement, will help UK suppliers compete for contracts and continue to support future defence requirements for steel.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428773/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T16:45:55.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428773/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428773/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-17","Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the likely effect of redundancies in the UK steel industry on the proportion of defence procurement that arises from UK businesses.","false","Biography information for Valerie  Vaz","Walsall South","Valerie Vaz","16653"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428774","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-20","<p>The Chancellor of the Exchequer will set out further details of the Joint Security Fund at the Spending Review on Wednesday 25 November.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428774/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:18:40.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428774/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428774/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-17","Defence: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, when his Department expects to know how much of the Joint Security Fund announced by the Chancellor of the Exchequer in July 2015 will be allocated to his Department.","false","Biography information for Mr Kevan Jones","North Durham","Mr Kevan Jones","16647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428775","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-23","<p>A number of options are being developed to meet the training demand for UK Reaper aircrew in the coming years. It is anticipated that initial training for some UK student aircrew will be conducted under contract by General Atomics at their North Dakota facility.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428775/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T17:24:13.8Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428775/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428775/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-17","USA: Unmanned Air Vehicles","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether he plans for UK personnel to train at or otherwise attend the new General Atomics unmanned aircraft business park being built in North Dakota.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","16740"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428776","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-23","<p>No UK Reapers have been flown on missions by US personnel or those of any other Coalition nation in Syria since January 2015. US personnel have operated UK Reaper aircraft a small number of times to aid with the launch and recovery of the aircraft only, not the mission itself. A Memorandum of Understanding has been agreed between the UK and US Air Forces which allows the US to request the use of UK Reaper aircraft to conduct missions and vice versa, though to date this has not occurred. Such use by the US would be subject to UK permissions.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428776/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T17:23:42.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428776/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428776/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-17","Syria: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether UK Reapers have been made available for use by the US or other coalition partners in Syria for operations since January 2015.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","16741"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428777","Department for Education","false","2015-11-24","<p>Data showing the numbers of students eligible for free school meals, going to individual universities, are not published by the department.</p><p>Destination measures data are published and show the overall percentage of key stage 5 students[1] eligible for free school meals[2] going into sustained[3] destinations at higher education institutions. The data also include the percentage going into sustained destinations at Russell group universities and Oxford and Cambridge.</p><p>Destination measures data for students eligible for free school meals are published for the years 2010/11 to 2013/14 and are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-destinations" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/statistics-destinations</a></p><br /><p>[1] Key stage 5 students are those entered for A level or other equivalent level 3 qualifications</p><p>[2] Eligible for free school meals at any time in year 11</p><p>[3] Sustained for 6 months (October to March)</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428777/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T14:59:23.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428777/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428777/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-17","Universities: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many pupils eligible for free school meals took up a place at each university in each year since 2005-06.","false","Biography information for Suella Braverman","Fareham","Suella Fernandes","16670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428778","Department for Education","false","2015-11-20","<p>There are now more, better-qualified teachers in Englandâs classrooms than ever before. In November 2014 there were 454,900 full time equivalent (FTE) teachers, up 5,200 from the previous year and up 13,100 from 2010. A record 96.6 per cent of all teachers now hold a degree or higher qualification.</p><p>Teacher vacancy rates have remained stable at around 1 per cent of all posts for over a decade, and retention rates have also remained stable over the same period. Approximately 90 per cent of teachers are in service in the year after they qualify, and 72 per cent of those who qualified in 2009 were still teaching 5 years later. Over the longer term, over 60 per cent of teachers remain in service 10 years after qualifying.</p><p>Nevertheless, we recognise that teacher recruitment is a challenge as the economy continues to strengthen and competition for new graduates intensifies; this is particularly true in certain areas of the country. We are taking steps to attract more top graduates and career changers into the profession, particularly in those core academic subjects that help children reach their potential. This includes offering generous financial incentives, such as tax-free bursaries of up to Â£30,000 for top graduates in priority subjects such as physics.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428778/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T11:31:37.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428778/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428778/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-17","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 16 November 2015 to Question 15281, what assessment she has made of the adequacy of the number of teachers trained in the last 10 years; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","16706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428779","Department for Education","false","2015-11-24","<p>The contractual acceptance criteria for reception baseline suppliers had two levels related to the volume of schools recruited. If fewer than four suppliers met the 10% threshold, suppliers were still accepted if they had recruited more than 1,000 schools. All approved suppliers met the minimum volume criteria.</p><p>The reception baseline contract is published online at: <a href="https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive/contract/1656259/" target="_blank">https://data.gov.uk/data/contracts-finder-archive/contract/1656259/</a></p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428779/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T16:50:02.173Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428779/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428779/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-11-17","Primary Education: Assessments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 12 November to Question 14860, whether all of the providers approved by her Department to provide baseline assessment for primary schools reached the qualifying 10 per cent threshold for providers by the 30 April 2015 deadline.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","16662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428780","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-24","<p>The basis on which Chinese companies will invest in the Hinkley Point C project is set out in the strategic investor agreement agreed between EDF and CGN in October. The terms of this agreement are a matter for EDF.</p><br /><p>Operators of new nuclear power stations are required to have a Funded Decommissioning Programme (FDP) approved by the Secretary of State before nuclear related construction can begin. The FDP sets out how a new nuclear operator will make secure financial provision for decommissioning their power station and managing and disposing of its waste without recourse to the taxpayer.</p><br /><p>Operators of nuclear power stations are also required to put in place insurance or other financial security to meet their nuclear third party liabilities.</p><br /> <br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428780/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T17:22:28.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428780/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428780/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428780/answer/previousversion/31301","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-17","Hinkley Point C Power Station: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether the agreement signed with China to fund Hinckley Point C nuclear reactor includes funding from China for (a) decommissioning costs and (b) emergency clean-up costs.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","16727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428781","Department of Health","false","2015-11-20","<p>Since the United Kingdom has a residence based healthcare system, a person who is not ordinarily resident in the UK, including a British national expatriate, is chargeable for any National Health Service hospital services they receive during visits to the UK, unless an exemption category applies, as set out in Regulations. Therefore, entitlement to free NHS care is not linked to the payment of UK taxes.</p><br /><p>Being ordinarily resident in the UK means, in relation to British citizens, living here on a lawful, properly settled basis for the time being. A person can be ordinarily resident in more than one country at a time, depending on their individual circumstances. <br></p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428781/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:38:58.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428781/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428781/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-17","Health Services: British Nationals Abroad","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether British expatriates who pay income tax in the UK will be charged for medical treatment in the UK.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","16728"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428782","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-23","<p>The Department of Energy and Climate Changeâs expenditure in each successive year 2010-11 to 2014-15 and for the categories identified (a) temporary staff; (b) consultants; (d) administration and (e) marketing and advertising and as a percentage of each yearâs total budget for the core Department is given in the table attached. We have interpreted (c) ânon-payroll staffâ to mean âtemporary staff and âconsultantsâ.</p><br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428782/answer","Question 16707 - Table of DECC staff costs.docx","Question 16707 - Table of DECC staff costs.docx","DECC temp/consultant/admin/marketing staff costs","DECC temp/consultant/admin/marketing staff costs",,"2015-11-23T16:01:49.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428782/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428782/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428782/answer/previousversion/31299","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-17","Department of Energy and Climate Change: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what her Department's spending on (a) temporary agency staff, (b) consultants, (c) non-payroll staff, (d) administration and (e) marketing and advertising was in (i) 2014-15 prices and (ii) as a share of her Department's total budget in each year since 2010-11.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","16707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428783","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-24","<p>The Department does not publish full-year forecast for departmental expenditure limits (DEL) spending. The Office for Budget Responsibility (<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/OBR" target="_blank">OBR</a>) forecast underspends in DEL as part of their Economic and Fiscal Outlook which is due to be published on 25th November alongside the Autumn Statement. Outturn data will be published in the Departmentâs Annual Report and Accounts planned for publication by the end of June, before Summer recess.</p><p>The forecast of total Annually Managed Expenditure spend for 2015-16 as at March Budget 2015 and Summer Budget 2015 is shown in DECC's Main Estimate; forecasts are currently being updated for the Supplementary Estimate which is due to be published in February:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/441360/PU_1815_Main_Estimates_book_WEB.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/441360/PU_1815_Main_Estimates_book_WEB.pdf</a>.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428783/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T13:16:25.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428783/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428783/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428783/answer/previousversion/31300","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-17","Department of Energy and Climate Change: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what her Department's expected underspend is against departmental expenditure limits in the current fiscal year; and what her Department's latest forecast of total AME spend is for this year compared to forecasts at the time of the (a) Summer Budget 2015 and (b) March Budget 2015.","false","Biography information for Lisa Nandy","Wigan","Lisa Nandy","16708"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428784","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-25","<p>In England between 2010 and 2014, support for organic farmers was provided under the Organic Entry Level Stewardship scheme (OELS) and Organic Higher Level Stewardship scheme (OHLS), which were set up under the Rural Development Programme for England (RDPE). The following table provides details of the annual funding provided during this period. Organic farmers were also eligible for payments under the Single Payment Scheme.</p><br /><p><strong>OELS and OHLS funding in England 2010-2014</strong>:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Annual funding for OELS:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong> Annual funding for OHLS:</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p></td><td><p>Â£1,986,129</p></td><td><p>Â£17,454,578</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p></td><td><p>Â£4,285,822</p></td><td><p>Â£21,059,841</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p></td><td><p>Â£6,088,660</p></td><td><p>Â£24,443,405</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013</p></td><td><p>Â£7,503,473</p></td><td><p>Â£27,495,231</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>Â£8,665,682</p></td><td><p>Â£29,486,762</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Total Funding:</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Â£28,529,766</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Â£119,939,817</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>Footnote 1: Because agriculture is a devolved matter, separate schemes operate in other UK countries. Data on other funding provided is available from devolved administrations.</p><br /><p>Footnote 2: These data include payments to organic farmers under conventional land management options in combined organic and conventional agreements and include payments for existing and new agreements each year.</p><br /><p>Footnote 3: RDPE funding comprises EU funding allocated under the CAP for England and relevant Exchequer match funding.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428784/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T10:31:16.04Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428784/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428784/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-11-17","Organic Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how much support from EU agricultural funding has been awarded to UK organic food producers in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","16720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428785","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-20","<p>In 2012 Defra published research on the extent of use and humaneness of snares in England and Wales. Ministers are currently considering options.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428785/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T12:06:57.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428785/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428785/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-11-17","Foxes: Trapping","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when she plans to publish her Department's new code of practice on the use of fox snares.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","16699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428786","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-20","<p>We have been working with Sub-Group members to finalise the Hen Harrier Action Plan with a view to publishing it shortly.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428786/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T12:53:59.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428786/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428786/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-11-17","Birds of Prey: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, when she will publish the Joint Hen Harrier Recovery Plan.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","16704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428787","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-11-25","<p>The Government welcomed the recent Farm Animal Welfare Committee (FAWC) Opinion on CCTV in slaughterhouses. FAWC did not recommend using animal welfare charities or voluntary organisations to monitor CCTV in slaughterhouses.</p><br /><p>However, the report highlighted that CCTV was a useful management tool for food business operators and the Government is keen to see the minority of abattoirs still without any form of CCTV move quickly to voluntarily adopt its use. We welcome the recent industry statement which addresses one of the FAWC recommendations that the slaughter industry should produce a common set of good practice protocols for the review, evaluation and use of CCTV footage.</p><p>.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428787/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T11:31:46.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428787/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428787/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-11-17","Slaughterhouses: CCTV","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what her policy is on utilising the skills of animal welfare charities and voluntary organisations to monitor CCTV in slaughterhouses.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","16655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428788","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-20","<p>I refer the hon. Member to my answer of 16 November 2015 (PQ 15345).</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428788/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:54:17.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428788/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428788/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-17","Foreign and Commonwealth Office: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department is taking to embed the Family Test into its policy making.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","16681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428789","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-25","<p>Since the publication of the Foreign and Commonwealth Office-funded independent report on Children in Military Custody in June 2012, there has been some progress on the issue of children held in military detention. This includes a pilot to use summons instead of night-time arrests, changes to standard operating procedures on methods of restraint, and steps to reduce the amount of time a child can be detained before seeing a judge. There has also been a reduction in the use of solitary confinement and an increase in the use of Arabic to give notifications of arrest.</p><p>While we welcome the improvements to date, we continue to press the Israeli authorities to make further progress on this important issue.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428789/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T15:26:51.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428789/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428789/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-17","Palestinians: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many of the (a) core recommendations and (b) specific recommendations of his Department's report entitled Children in Military Custody, published in June 2012, the Israeli government has implemented.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","16735"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428790","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-19","<p>As my honourable Friend will know, Argentina held an inconclusive first round of Presidential elections last month. A second round is due to take place on 22 November.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428790/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-19T17:35:03.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428790/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428790/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-17","Falkland Islands","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the implications for the Falkland Islands of the results of the recent Argentinian presidential election.","false","Biography information for Antoinette Sandbach","Eddisbury","Antoinette Sandbach","16661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428791","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-25","The United Kingdom contributes to the EU budget as a whole, not to individual elements of it. The initial European External Action Service (EEAS) budget in 2011 was â¬464 million. â¬441 million of this was existing money transferred from the Commission and Council Secretariat. The EEAS budget was â¬489 million in 2012, â¬509 million in 2013 and â¬519 million in 2014. Over this period, the UK's pre-abatement financing share was 14.5% (outturn) in 2011, 15.3% in 2012, 15.5% in 2013, and 15.4% in 2014 based on the latest budgets for those years. The UK has been clear in arguing for restraint in the EEAS budget at a time when difficult spending decisions are being taken by member states and we continue to remind the EEAS of its commitment to resource neutrality.","Aylesbury","Mr David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428791/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T15:54:22.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428791/answer","Biography information for Sir David Lidington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428791/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-17","European External Action Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the UK contribution to the European External Action Service has been in each year since its creation; and what proportion of the European External Action Service's overall budget the UK has contributed in each such year.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","16664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428792","Department of Health","false","2015-11-20","<p>There has not been a formal review of the adequacy of suicide prevention support for men and women. However, we published a national strategy, Preventing Suicide in England: a cross-Government strategy to save lives in 2012. I announced in a Westminster Hall Debate on 19 November 2015 that this strategy was a dynamic one, being reviewed and refreshed regularly. We continue to monitor and track trends in suicide and work with organisations across Government and industry and with a range of stakeholder organisations to implement the national strategy. We publish an annual report on our progress. The next annual report will be published early next year.</p><br /><p>The Department provides financial support to the National Suicide Prevention Alliance consisting of a range of organisations concerned with suicide prevention which provides expert advice on implementing the national strategy.</p><br />","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428792/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T11:54:32.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428792/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428792/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-17","Suicide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent review his Department has conducted into the adequacy of suicide prevention support for (a) men and (b) women; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","16703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428793","Department of Health","false","2015-11-25","<br /><p>Dental amalgam has been in use for over 150 years to restore teeth in millions of patients and, apart from rare instances of hypersensitivity, no adverse reactions have been identified. Alternative dental restorative materials are not so easily, quickly and reliably placed. Neither are they so durable. Due to improvements in oral health, the number of restorations is decreasing with the result that the safe management and disposal of dental amalgam is more easily achieved.</p><br /><p>The World Health Organization report <em>Future Use of Materials for Dental Restorations November 2009</em> concluded that dental amalgam remains a dental restorative material of choice in the absence of an ideal alternative. The Department concurs with the conclusions of the report which can be found at:</p><br /><p><a href="http://www.who.int/oral_health/publications/dental_material_2011.pdf" target="_blank">http://www.who.int/oral_health/publications/dental_material_2011.pdf</a></p><p><strong></strong></p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428793/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T12:35:26.887Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428793/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428793/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-17","Dental Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the appropriateness of the use of amalgam in dental fillings.","false","Biography information for Dr Matthew Offord","Hendon","Dr Matthew Offord","16715"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428794","Department of Health","false","2015-11-20","<br /><p>Information on the number of patients who were admitted to mental health hospitals outside their home local authority in St Helens North constituency, Merseyside and the United Kingdom in each of the last five years is not available. However, information on the number of people in non-specialist mental health beds treated out of area between September 2014 and July 2015 is set out in the attached table: the number of people in non-specialist mental health bed, placed out of area at the end of the month, for England and Mersey Care NHS Trust, September 2014-July 2015.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428794/answer","Number of people in non specialist mental health beds- out of area September 2014-July 2015.xlsx","Number of people in non specialist mental health beds- out of area September 2014-July 2015.xlsx","Non specialist mental health beds- out of area","Non specialist mental health beds- out of area",,"2015-11-20T14:33:45.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428794/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428794/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-11-17","Psychiatric Hospitals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many patients in (a) St Helens North constituency, (b) Merseyside and (c) the UK were admitted to mental health hospitals outside of their local authority area in the last five years.","false","Biography information for Conor McGinn","St Helens North","Conor McGinn","16709"
