"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428830","Department for International Development","false","2015-11-20","<p>The Family Test does not apply to DFID's work as its scope is limited to domestic policy areas.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428830/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T12:58:38.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428830/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428830/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-11-17","Department for International Development: Families","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to embed the Family Test into its policy making.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","16712"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428831","Department for International Development","false","2015-11-25","<p>The last main supply estimate was published in July 2015, and is available online here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/main-supply-estimates-2015-to-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/main-supply-estimates-2015-to-2016</a>.</p><br /><p>DFID is currently forecasting to fully utilise its departmental expenditure limits (DEL) and annually managed expenditure (AME) as allocated and approved by Parliament.</p><br />","Putney","Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428831/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T17:53:22.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428831/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428831/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-11-17","Department for International Development: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what (a) the amount of any underspend expected against departmental expenditure limits in the current fiscal year and (b) her Department's latest forecast of total annually managed expenditure spend for this year is; and what the forecasts were for those sums at the time of the Summer Budget 2015 and March Budget 2015.","false","Biography information for Ms Diane Abbott","Hackney North and Stoke Newington","Ms Diane Abbott","16658"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428832","Department for International Development","false","2015-11-20","<p>Since 2011, the UK has provided Â£163 million of core funding to the UN High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR) to deliver protection and assistance to refugees globally. The UK works with the Government of Iraq, Kurdish Regional Government, the UN and the international community to support the rights of all minorities and to ensure our aid reaches those in greatest need.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428832/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T13:02:35.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428832/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428832/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-11-17","Iran: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to support refugees from Iran; and what recent assessment she has made of the safety of Iranian refuges in Iraq.","false","Biography information for Dr Tania Mathias","Twickenham","Dr Tania Mathias","16691"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428833","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-11-25","<p>Ministers in the Northern Ireland Office have not had any direct discussions with the NI Executive about (a) licensing of road hauliers and (b) tackling transportation of illicit fuel. Matters relating to (a) the road hauliers and (b) tackling transportation of illicit fuel are for the DVA and HMRC respectively.</p><br />","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428833/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T13:24:34.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428833/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428833/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-11-17","Roads: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with the Northern Ireland executive about (a) the licensing of road hauliers and (b) tackling transportation of illicit fuel.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","16635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428834","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-23","<p>No specific assessment has been made of the effectiveness of cross border co-operation in reducing the level of fuel laundering. However, tax gap figures published on 22 October 2015 in the document at the link below estimates the market share for all illicit diesel in GB mainland as or just under 1%, and 8% in NI for 2013/14. This amounts to about Â£100m for UK as a whole. Petrol fraud is negligible.</p><p><br> <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/measuring-tax-gaps" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/measuring-tax-gaps</a> <br> <br></p><p>HMRC fights fraud on a wide range of fronts, from special units performing thousands of roadside checks to raiding laundering plants. Additionally, the UK has recently implemented an improved marker for rebated fuel, which will make it much harder to launder marked fuel and sell it at a profit. Ireland has also introduced the same new marker as the UK.</p><br /><p>HMRC works closely with the Revenue Commissioners in the Republic of Ireland to fight fuel fraud, including regular exchange of information and joint operational activity.</p><br />","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428834/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T15:09:49.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428834/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428834/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-17","Fuels: Tax Evasion","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment has been made of the effectiveness of cross border co-operation in reducing the level of fuel laundering.","false","Biography information for Nigel Dodds","Belfast North","Mr Nigel Dodds","16636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428835","Department for Transport","false","2015-11-20","<p>All maritime security requirements are risk informed and are kept under constant review. The Department for Transport (DfT) works closely with ports, ferry operators and other agencies to ensure the safety of the travelling public.</p><br /><p>The DfT also has a set of comprehensive maritime security requirements which port facilities and ships are required to implement, with a well-established monitoring and oversight programme in place to ensure compliance with this regime.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428835/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T13:17:09.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428835/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428835/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-11-17","Ports: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether a security review has been initiated for the purpose of strengthening port security between Northern Ireland and Scotland.","false","Biography information for Richard Arkless","Dumfries and Galloway","Richard  Arkless","16646"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428836","Scotland Office","false","2015-11-23","<p>Protective security postures for public events are coordinated across the United Kingdom by the UK National Counter-Terrorism Policing Headquarters; the Police Service of Scotland forms part of the national counter-terrorism police network. The UK National Counter-Terrorism Policing Headquarters is providing guidance to ground safety staff for sports stadia across the UK. The Home Office is also in regular contact with the Scottish Government on counter-terrorism measures.</p><br />","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428836/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T15:45:48.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428836/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428836/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-11-17","Sports: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what recent discussions he has had with the (a) Scottish Government and (b) Scottish FA on strengthening security at Scottish stadiums and sporting events.","false","Biography information for Richard Arkless","Dumfries and Galloway","Richard  Arkless","16672"
