"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432117","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-11-25","<p><em>Building a Prosperous and United Community,</em> the âEconomic Pactâ signed by the Government and the Northern Ireland Executive in 2013, recognised the need to examine the potential to devolve additional fiscal powers to Northern Ireland.</p><p>As a result, the Executive is examining the treatment of a range of taxes. The Government will consider any proposals put forward.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432117/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T15:46:01.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432117/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432117/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-11-17","Income Tax: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with Cabinet colleagues on income tax assignment to Northern Ireland; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Graham Allen","Nottingham North","Mr Graham Allen","902252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432118","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-11-25","<p>Tackling low pay is part of the Government's plan to move to a higher wage, lower tax and lower welfare society.</p><p>100,000 low-paid people in Northern Ireland, 13 per cent of the workforce, will directly benefit from the National Living Wage from April next year.</p><p>A full-time worker on the current National Minimum Wage will be Â£1,200 better off as a result.</p><p>The Governmentâs plan is working. Official figures published last week show that weekly earnings for full-time employees in Northern Ireland were up 5.4 per cent over the year. The highest growth rate of all regions in the UK.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432118/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T15:52:34.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432118/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432118/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-11-17","Low Pay: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what steps the Government is taking to tackle low pay in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","902256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432119","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-11-25","<p>I regularly discuss national security issues with Cabinet colleagues.</p><p>The National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review published this week, confirm that tackling terrorism in all its forms continues to be one of the Governmentâs highest priorities.</p><p>We will increase funding for counter-terrorism by 30% in real terms over this Parliament.</p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432119/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T15:41:08.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432119/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432119/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-11-17","Intelligence Services: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with Cabinet colleagues on ensuring that Northern Ireland benefits from the Government's planned expansion of the intelligence agencies.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","902248"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432120","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-11-25","<p>Support for charities which provide sexual health advice and services in Northern Ireland is a matter for the Northern Ireland Assembly. Ministers in the Northern Ireland Office have received no representations.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432120/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-25T15:43:35.46Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432120/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/432120/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-11-17","Genito-urinary Medicine: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what representations she has received on support for charities which provide sexual health advice and services in Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","902249"
