"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428360","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-23","<p>The <em>Energy Efficiency (Private Rented Property)(England and Wales) Regulations 2015</em> were made in March this year following a full public consultation, and establish an EPC minimum of E for domestic and non-domestic private rented sector properties from April 2018.</p><br /><p>Officials in the Department liaise regularly with the insulation industry, local authorities, and other stakeholders on a range of energy efficiency issues including the minimum EPC standards for the private rented sector. Discussions have also been held recently with French officials about domestic energy efficiency issues including minimum standards.</p><br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428360/answer",,,,,"16464 ; 16465","2015-11-23T11:58:50.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428360/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428360/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428360/answer/previousversion/30998","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-16","Private Rented Housing: Energy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what recent discussions she has had with her European counterparts about minimum EPC standards for the private rented sector.","false","Biography information for Graham P Jones","Hyndburn","Graham Jones","16463"
