"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428363","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-24","<p>Universal Credit claimants, who are expected to look for work, must take all reasonable action they can to become employed. Any requirements placed on the claimant will be based on a discussion with their work coach, taking into account the individualâs circumstances, including any offer of employment they may have received.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428363/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T13:13:46.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428363/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428363/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-16","Universal Credit: Disqualification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will take steps to ensure that universal credit claimants are not sanctioned in the period between accepting an offer of employment and starting employment.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","16361"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428364","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-19","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the Minister for Reserves (Mr Brazier) on 26 March 2015 to Questions 225369, 225370 and 225371 to the hon. Member for Moray (Mr Robertson) and confirm that there continues to be no Typhoon Tranche 3 aircraft in storage. There are currently a total of 92 Typhoon aircraft in the Forward Fleet and 39 aircraft in the Sustainment Fleet.</p><p>Deliveries of the 40 Tranche 3A aircraft ordered for the RAF are continuing. A decision was taken in July 2014 by the Eurofighter Typhoon Partner Nations not to proceed with a follow-on order of Tranche 3B aircraft.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428364/answer","20150326_225369_Miltary_Aircraft.docx","20150326_225369_Miltary_Aircraft.docx","QnA extract on Miltary Aircraft","QnA extract on Miltary Aircraft","16473","2015-11-19T16:01:38.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428364/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428364/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-16","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what his plans are for the Tranche 3 a Typhoon aircraft; and how many such aircraft are in storage.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","16476"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428365","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-19","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the Minister for Reserves (Mr Brazier) on 26 March 2015 to Questions 225369, 225370 and 225371 to the hon. Member for Moray (Mr Robertson) and confirm that there continues to be no Typhoon Tranche 3 aircraft in storage. There are currently a total of 92 Typhoon aircraft in the Forward Fleet and 39 aircraft in the Sustainment Fleet.</p><p>Deliveries of the 40 Tranche 3A aircraft ordered for the RAF are continuing. A decision was taken in July 2014 by the Eurofighter Typhoon Partner Nations not to proceed with a follow-on order of Tranche 3B aircraft.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428365/answer","20150326_225369_Miltary_Aircraft.docx","20150326_225369_Miltary_Aircraft.docx","QnA extract on Miltary Aircraft","QnA extract on Miltary Aircraft","16476","2015-11-19T16:01:38.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428365/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428365/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-16","European Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the current status is of the purchase Tranche 3 b Typhoon aircraft; and how many such aircraft his Department plans to purchase.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","16473"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428366","Department for International Development","false","2015-11-20","<p>The UK has been at the forefront of the response to the crisis in Syria and the region. We have pledged over Â£1.1 billion to date, our largest ever response to a single humanitarian crisis. We are the second largest bilateral donor after the US.</p><p>DFID is supporting 11 implementing partners to prepare and respond to the onset of winter across Syria, Lebanon and Jordan. This financial year, we have provided Â£221 million to these 11 partners to support their emergency programmes, of which Â£12.9 million has been committed for specific winter response activities such as the provision of warm clothing, thermal blankets, fuel and cash to support thousands of vulnerable families across the region.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428366/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T13:15:51.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428366/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428366/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-11-16","Syria: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what support her Department is providing to aid agencies and international partners to prepare Syrian refugee camps for winter.","false","Biography information for Dawn Butler","Brent Central","Dawn Butler","16498"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428367","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-24","<p>Officials from the British High Commission regularly meet with political and civil society groups, including the Tamil National Alliance, to discuss political issues in Sri Lanka. We will continue to monitor the situation of detainees held under the Prevention of Terrorism Act closely and to raise issues of ongoing concern with the Sri Lankan government.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428367/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T18:02:36.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428367/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428367/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-16","Sri Lanka: Political Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent representations the British High Commission in Colombo has received from (a) the Tamil National Alliance and (b) Tamil civil society groups on the treatment of Tamil political prisoners in Sri Lanka.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","16378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428368","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-24","We regularly raise matters of concern with the Sri Lankan government, including the Prevention of Terrorism Act and the detention of prisoners without trial. I met Sri Lankan Foreign Minister, the Honourable Mangala Samaraweera MP, on 14 September in Geneva. I was encouraged by our discussion and by his speech to the UN Human Rights Council. Amongst other commitments, he told members of the UN Human Rights Council that the Sri Lankan government would review and repeal the Prevention of Terrorism Act and replace it with anti-terrorism legislation in line with contemporary international best practices. We will continue to monitor closely the situation of detainees held under the Prevention of Terrorism Act, and to raise issues of ongoing concern with the Sri Lankan government.","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428368/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T17:49:06.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428368/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428368/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-16","Sri Lanka: Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his Sri Lankan counterpart on the application of the Prevention of Terrorism Act 1978 in Sri Lanka.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","16355"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428369","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-24","<p>We noted that on 17 November the hunger strike by Tamil detainees was temporarily suspended until 15 December. We regularly raise matters of concern with the Sri Lankan government, including the detention of prisoners without trial. Our policy is unchanged and we remain committed to working closely with the Sri Lankan government and international partners to support the implementation of the commitments made by Sri Lanka at the UN Human Rights Council in September, and in the UN Human Rights Council resolution of 1 October.</p>","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428369/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T17:54:41.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428369/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428369/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-16","Sri Lanka: Political Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the implications for his policies of reports that Tamil political prisoners have been on hunger strike in Sri Lanka; and if he will make a statement.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","16356"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428370","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-24","We regularly raise matters of concern with the Sri Lankan government, including the Prevention of Terrorism Act and the detention of Tamil political prisoners without trial. I met Sri Lankan Foreign Minister, the Honourable Mangala Samaraweera MP, on 14 September in Geneva. I was encouraged by our discussion and by his speech to the UN Human Rights Council. He told members of the UN Human Rights Council that the Sri Lankan government would review and repeal the Prevention of Terrorism Act and replace it with anti-terrorism legislation in line with contemporary international best practices. I have also been encouraged by the recent announcements that bail has been granted to 39 prisoners being held under the Prevention of Terrorism Act.","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428370/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T17:58:17.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428370/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428370/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-16","Sri Lanka: Political Prisoners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his Sri Lankan counterpart on the detention of Tamil political prisoners in Sri Lanka.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","16357"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428371","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-11-24","We warmly welcomed the resolution on promoting reconciliation, accountability and human rights which was co-sponsored by Sri Lanka and adopted by the UN Human Rights Council on 1 October. Since President Sirisena came to power in January, there have been improvements in the human rights situation in Sri Lanka, including on freedom of expression, some return of military held land, and improved relations between different communities. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office will provide a further assessment in our 2015 Annual Human Rights and Democracy Report. We regularly raise matters of concern with the Sri Lankan government, including the detention of Tamil political prisoners without trial. We have been encouraged by the recent announcements that bail has been granted to 39 prisoners being held under the Prevention of Terrorism Act.","East Devon","Mr Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428371/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T18:00:05.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428371/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugo Swire","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428371/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-11-16","Sri Lanka: Human Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent assessment he has made of the (a) human rights situation in Sri Lanka and (b) detention of Tamil political prisoners in that country.","true","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","16358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428372","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-11-23","<p>From April 2017 the Government will remove automatic entitlement to housing support for 18-21 year olds in Universal Credit. This rule, which will apply to new claims from those who are out of work, will ensure parity with those young adults who are in employment but are unable to afford to leave home. However, there will be circumstances where it is reasonable to support a young person in living independently. The Department is discussing this issue with key stakeholders in order to determine which groups might be exempt from the general rule. This includes many organisations that provide supported accommodation for young people. It is too early to confirm the outcome from those discussions.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428372/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T15:57:53.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428372/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428372/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-11-16","Universal Credit: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether 18 to 21 year olds who live in supported accommodation will be able to claim the housing element of universal credit when they move out of supported accommodation.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","16318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428373","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-23","<p>The Department recognises the potential for storage to help us use energy more flexibly and decarbonise our energy system cost effectively, alongside interconnection and demand-side response (DSR). As such, DECC is investigating the potential barriers to the deployment of energy storage. We are carefully considering possible mitigating actions, focussing in the first instance on removing regulatory barriers to energy storage. The re-classification of energy storage is one of the options we are considering. We plan to conduct a consultation and call for evidence in due course.</p><br /> <br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428373/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T15:14:43.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428373/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428373/answer",,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-16","Electricity: Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether she has given consideration to re-classifying electricity storage vessels to enable distribution network operators to utilise such vessels without paying generation charges.","false","Biography information for Alan Brown","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Alan Brown","16370"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428374","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-11-23","<p>There have been no discussions with the Secretary of State for Defence on the release of documents at Swadlincote. The Northern Ireland Office has no records held at Swadlincote.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428374/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-23T12:53:15.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428374/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428374/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-11-16","Public Records: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with the Secretary of State for Defence on the release of documents relating to Northern Ireland held at Swadlincote under the 30-year rule.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","16335"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428375","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-11-20","<p>The Government is focused on delivering a successful renegotiation.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428375/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T11:13:01.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428375/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428375/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-11-16","UK Membership of EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what the implications are for the (a) PEACE and (b) INTERREG IVA programmes in (i) the UK and (ii) Northern Ireland of a UK decision to leave the EU.","false","Biography information for Dr Alasdair McDonnell","Belfast South","Dr Alasdair McDonnell","16321"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428376","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-11-20","<p>DECC ministers and officials meet with energy companies on a regular basis to discuss a range of issues.</p><br /><p>The government expects suppliers to make sure any reductions in the costs of supplying energy are passed to consumers.</p><p><br> <br></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428376/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-20T14:26:14.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428376/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428376/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428376/answer/previousversion/30994","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-11-16","Energy: Prices","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what representations she has made to energy companies to ensure they pass on reductions in the wholesale price of gas and electricity to the consumer.","false","Biography information for Wayne David","Caerphilly","Wayne David","16468"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428377","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-11-24","<p>The Ministry of Defence is in the planning stage of its RAF100 Campaign and intends to hold a National commemoration to mark the 100th anniversary of the founding of the RAF. A full list of events and activities will be published in 2017.</p><br />","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428377/answer",,,,,,"2015-11-24T16:42:25.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428377/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428377/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-11-16","Air Force: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans his Department has to hold national events to commemorate the 100th anniversary of the founding of the RAF in 2018.","false","Biography information for Edward Argar","Charnwood","Edward Argar","16345"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428378","HM Treasury","false","2015-11-24","<p>The information is not available. HM Revenue and Customs does not routinely record whether a student is in full time education.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428378/answer",,,,,"16423","2015-11-24T14:46:13.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428378/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/428378/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-11-16","Students: Self-employed","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the cost to HM Revenue and Customs of administering and enforcing self-employed registration for students in full-time education earning less than the Personal Allowance.","false","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","Wealden","Nusrat Ghani","16434"
